WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:06.658
.

00:06.702 --> 00:08.965
- Previously on "Colony"...

00:09.009 --> 00:10.662
- I represent a resistance
group based outside the wall.

00:10.706 --> 00:12.186
We have a RAP.

00:12.229 --> 00:14.579
Just needs the gauntlet to tap into their communication.

00:15.885 --> 00:17.104
- We've got the target.
Get out of there.

00:17.147 --> 00:18.322
- She can't--she can't be dead.

00:18.366 --> 00:19.715
She never told us
where her base was.

00:19.758 --> 00:21.021
She never told us
anything.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.935
- A recovery operation
for the gauntlet.

00:22.979 --> 00:24.328
We'll find it

00:24.372 --> 00:26.026
through border inspections
during the evacuation.

00:26.069 --> 00:28.332
- I got the call last night.

00:28.376 --> 00:31.074
- Dare I ask what
they're planning instead?

00:31.118 --> 00:33.598
- Total rendition.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.645
- I'm being transitioned
into a position

00:36.688 --> 00:38.081
with the Global Authority.

00:38.125 --> 00:41.128
I've carved out
a place for you on my staff.

00:41.171 --> 00:44.174
- We need to leave the bloc.
We could contact Snyder.

00:44.218 --> 00:45.871
If we make a trade,
do you have the juice

00:45.915 --> 00:46.872
to get us out of the bloc?

00:46.916 --> 00:48.265
- I want to come with you.

00:48.309 --> 00:53.053
I just don't want
to be a rat anymore.

00:53.096 --> 00:54.358
- I'm staying.

00:54.402 --> 00:56.056
When you get outside,
you need to make contact

00:56.099 --> 00:58.058
with Noa's people
and get this to them.

01:05.108 --> 01:12.333
♪

01:52.155 --> 01:54.157
- Ow.

01:54.201 --> 01:56.246
Ow. Ow, ow.

01:57.813 --> 02:00.555
- I don't know when I turned
into a short-order cook.

02:00.598 --> 02:03.297
- It's because you're useless
at all the other chores.

02:03.340 --> 02:04.602
- "Useless" seems like

02:04.646 --> 02:07.083
an unnecessarily hurtful
choice of words.

02:07.127 --> 02:09.390
- You dyed all
my T-shirts pink.

02:09.433 --> 02:11.957
- What am I,
a laundry service?

02:18.181 --> 02:19.661
How's "Treasure Island"?

02:19.704 --> 02:22.446
- I don't really trust
Long John Silver.

02:22.490 --> 02:24.883
- That's a good instinct.

02:27.321 --> 02:29.366
- Good morning.

02:34.676 --> 02:35.546
- Gross.

02:37.679 --> 02:39.463
- If either of you
wants more privacy,

02:39.507 --> 02:41.987
there are tools in the garage
and wood in the forest.

02:42.031 --> 02:44.033
You can build your own house.

02:45.208 --> 02:48.298
- You two missed another
beautiful sunrise this morning.

02:48.342 --> 02:51.214
- Mm, I wouldn't say
that we missed it.

03:01.050 --> 03:03.095
It's early today.

03:03.139 --> 03:04.967
- We got to move.

03:05.010 --> 03:08.927
♪

03:08.971 --> 03:11.669
- Get 'em in the shelter.

03:11.713 --> 03:16.587
♪

03:34.257 --> 03:36.912
It's coming up on the mark.

03:38.087 --> 03:40.698
- It should turn around in...

03:40.742 --> 03:44.441
three, two, one.

03:48.271 --> 03:49.881
Should we run?

03:49.925 --> 03:52.144
- Hold.

03:52.188 --> 03:59.413
♪

04:06.115 --> 04:08.378
- Why did it break
the pattern?

04:08.422 --> 04:11.076
- It crossed
the survey line.

04:11.120 --> 04:14.297
♪

04:18.345 --> 04:22.523
♪

04:30.661 --> 04:34.012
- Think it was responding
to something?

04:34.056 --> 04:35.449
- There's no way to know.

04:35.492 --> 04:38.495
- Maybe we should move
to the backup cabin.

04:39.453 --> 04:41.106
- It didn't come
in this direction.

04:41.150 --> 04:44.284
And even if it does, we've
rigged every inch of this place

04:44.327 --> 04:46.286
with booby traps and alarms.

04:48.679 --> 04:51.856
It still beats LA, right?

04:57.993 --> 05:05.000
♪

05:25.499 --> 05:27.457
- I got one!

05:27.501 --> 05:29.154
All right.

05:29.198 --> 05:30.373
That's it.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.332
Keep the tension on it.

05:32.375 --> 05:34.638
Don't jerk it.

05:34.682 --> 05:36.640
That's it. That's it.
Keep your tip up.

05:36.684 --> 05:40.862
Strip line, strip line.
Don't jerk it.

05:40.905 --> 05:42.429
That's right.

05:42.472 --> 05:44.344
That's it--tip up.

05:44.387 --> 05:49.000
There we go.
Almost. Almost.

05:49.044 --> 05:50.828
Oh-oh!

05:50.872 --> 05:53.091
There he is.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.399
It's a big one.

05:56.443 --> 05:58.880
- Gonna be delicious.

05:58.923 --> 06:00.577
All right.

06:02.013 --> 06:03.363
Look at that.

06:05.234 --> 06:08.237
Ahh.
Ha ha ha!

06:08.280 --> 06:10.544
You're a natural.

06:10.587 --> 06:14.330
- I like it here.

06:14.374 --> 06:17.202
- Yeah, me too.

06:21.424 --> 06:23.165
- As long as it's safe.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.648
- Sometimes I miss
seeing other kids.

06:28.518 --> 06:30.564
- Yeah, I know.

06:30.607 --> 06:33.305
At least you got
your brothers, right?

06:49.365 --> 06:52.281
This isn't gonna stop a drone.

06:52.324 --> 06:56.459
- There's a lot more than just
drones in these woods, love.

06:58.896 --> 07:01.159
- I feel like
a Masai tribeswoman.

07:01.203 --> 07:02.813
- Good.

07:02.857 --> 07:05.076
Those women walk 40 miles
across the Serengeti for water

07:05.120 --> 07:06.817
without complaining.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.580
[person speaking indistinctly
over radio]

07:30.624 --> 07:34.323
- 17, 19, 5,

07:34.366 --> 07:39.546
36, 22,

07:39.589 --> 07:44.812
86, 114.

07:50.731 --> 07:54.212
- Your daughter catches fish
faster than I can net 'em.

08:02.003 --> 08:04.745
- I have to show you something.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.921
I've been using
a radio direction finder.

08:08.400 --> 08:11.142
- It's basically just
a receiver with an S meter.

08:14.319 --> 08:16.887
I've been tracking
the number station,

08:16.931 --> 08:19.150
and one of the signals
is really strong,

08:19.194 --> 08:21.588
so I tried to triangulate
her position.

08:21.631 --> 08:23.328
She moves between
every broadcast,

08:23.372 --> 08:25.940
but if you assume
she's on foot...

08:27.681 --> 08:29.421
- You're gonna have
to explain this stuff.

08:29.465 --> 08:31.206
- She's close.

08:31.249 --> 08:32.642
Like, really close.

08:32.686 --> 08:34.905
- You want to try
and contact her.

08:36.341 --> 08:38.039
If we respond on the radio
she'll just change the station.

08:38.082 --> 08:39.780
That's what
they're trained to do.

08:39.823 --> 08:43.261
- Not if we tell her
that we have the gauntlet...

08:43.305 --> 08:46.700
and give her
someplace safe to meet.

08:46.743 --> 08:49.398
- You've just proved
that if we use the radio,

08:49.441 --> 08:51.008
we'll give away
our position.

08:51.052 --> 08:54.142
- You keep talking about how
important the gauntlet is,

08:54.185 --> 08:55.796
how it might be worth
everything that happened

08:55.839 --> 08:57.537
in the bloc,
but we're just sitting up here

08:57.580 --> 09:00.191
with that thing, doing nothing.

09:03.238 --> 09:08.809
♪

09:08.852 --> 09:10.724
- Your father's right.

09:10.767 --> 09:14.989
But this is amazing work.

09:15.032 --> 09:18.166
We just have to figure out
what to do with it.

09:18.209 --> 09:25.260
♪

09:28.959 --> 09:31.527
- Gin rummy.
Best of five.

09:31.571 --> 09:32.876
- I don't play with cheaters.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.617
For the last time,

09:34.661 --> 09:36.314
I was not cheating.

09:36.358 --> 09:37.446
Those were the rules.

09:37.489 --> 09:38.882
- Rules that
you made up to win,

09:38.926 --> 09:40.318
otherwise known
as cheating.

09:40.362 --> 09:42.407
- Well, it's not my fault
you're bad at cards.

09:43.757 --> 09:45.280
Young lady, I'll have you know

09:45.323 --> 09:48.892
that I won the Sherman Oaks
Municipal Poker tournament...

09:48.936 --> 09:51.242
twice.

09:54.419 --> 09:55.595
Where's Bram?

09:55.638 --> 09:58.728
- 5, 19,

09:58.772 --> 10:01.818
17, 22...

10:03.777 --> 10:05.387
What do you want?

10:05.430 --> 10:07.084
- Is it really healthy
for a young man

10:07.128 --> 10:08.999
to spend all of his time
listening to some lady

10:09.043 --> 10:10.784
read numbers on the radio?

10:10.827 --> 10:12.437
- Are you here to give me
the sex talk?

10:12.481 --> 10:14.875
- I would, but unless you've
fallen in love with a bear,

10:14.918 --> 10:16.659
I don't see that it's
gonna be of much use.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.314
- Well, then thanks
for stopping by.

10:20.794 --> 10:23.187
- I overheard you talking
to your parents.

10:27.322 --> 10:30.499
- The walls are thin.

10:30.542 --> 10:32.719
The point is
that you were right.

10:32.762 --> 10:35.373
You need to reach out
to the Resistance.

10:36.984 --> 10:40.596
- Why do you suddenly care
so much about the Resistance?

10:41.641 --> 10:45.470
- As much as I've enjoyed
our little mountain sojourn,

10:45.514 --> 10:47.951
we can't survive
up here forever.

10:47.995 --> 10:49.779
We'll either run out
of supplies,

10:49.823 --> 10:51.694
or one of the drones
will find us.

10:51.738 --> 10:54.131
- Or maybe a bear.

10:54.175 --> 10:56.177
♪

10:56.220 --> 11:00.311
- I'm just encouraging you
to pursue your hobby...

11:00.355 --> 11:03.140
for all our sakes.

11:03.184 --> 11:10.191
♪

11:10.844 --> 11:14.630
- Yes!
- You're cheating.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.153
- How many games
of gin rummy

11:16.197 --> 11:18.155
you think those kids
have played?

11:18.199 --> 11:20.767
- Enough to wear out the cards.

11:20.810 --> 11:22.290
- Gracie's a shark.

11:22.333 --> 11:24.248
She tried to play me
for a piece of chocolate

11:24.292 --> 11:27.687
the other day.

11:27.730 --> 11:28.949
- So Bram...

11:28.992 --> 11:31.734
- Yeah.
He's bored off his ass.

11:31.778 --> 11:33.388
I don't blame him.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.825
- He may be bored,
but he's still got a point.

11:35.869 --> 11:38.393
We can't stay here forever.

11:39.742 --> 11:42.049
Why not?

11:43.528 --> 11:45.008
What are we supposed to do,

11:45.052 --> 11:48.142
wander around the desert
looking for a Resistance camp?

11:49.317 --> 11:50.622
- I'm frustrated.

11:50.666 --> 11:53.103
A lot of people died
for that gauntlet.

12:01.895 --> 12:05.115
- You're right that
we can't expose ourselves.

12:05.159 --> 12:07.901
But there's
got to be another way.

12:15.430 --> 12:17.127
Okay.

12:21.305 --> 12:23.525
Okay, we'll try.

12:25.222 --> 12:29.313
But in the meantime,
this isn't so bad, right?

12:30.706 --> 12:34.318
I mean, we're like
Swiss Family Robinson.

12:35.145 --> 12:39.367
- Oh, hell, nothing's perfect.

12:42.805 --> 12:49.594
♪

12:49.638 --> 12:51.553
Hmm.

12:51.596 --> 12:54.338
Come here, you.

12:56.427 --> 12:57.777
Oh, come on.

13:01.650 --> 13:03.434
Mm.

13:03.478 --> 13:10.441
♪

13:20.800 --> 13:26.936
♪

13:26.980 --> 13:30.113
- I've got the kids.

13:54.746 --> 14:01.971
♪

14:07.411 --> 14:07.847
.

14:17.204 --> 14:20.381
- Drones.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.735
- Some kind of ship.
It crashed a few miles away.

14:26.778 --> 14:29.085
- The Hosts' first response
will be search and rescue,

14:29.129 --> 14:31.087
but then they're gonna
lock down the area.

14:31.131 --> 14:33.568
Did those drones spot us?
- I don't think so.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.352
- We got to get
out of here.

14:35.396 --> 14:37.441
- We're more likely to be
spotted on the move.

14:37.485 --> 14:40.575
- Yeah, and if those things go
into search

14:40.618 --> 14:42.011
- We need more information.

14:42.055 --> 14:43.491
I'll go up the mountain,

14:43.534 --> 14:45.406
see if I can get eyes
on that crash site,

14:45.449 --> 14:47.712
see if it's close enough that
the drones are gonna be on us.

14:50.759 --> 14:52.935
♪

14:52.979 --> 14:55.459
You're coming with me.
Why me?

14:55.503 --> 14:57.113
- 'Cause you're the only one
that might know something

14:57.157 --> 14:58.898
about that ship--
come on.

14:58.941 --> 15:06.122
♪

15:16.263 --> 15:18.047
- You know, in my experience,

15:18.091 --> 15:20.354
you don't have to work so hard
to find problems.

15:20.397 --> 15:22.182
They usually come
and find you.

15:22.225 --> 15:24.358
Less talking, more walking.

15:24.401 --> 15:25.750
- I'm doing my best.

15:25.794 --> 15:27.622
Your legs
are, like, nine feet long.

15:34.803 --> 15:37.762
You ever heard of a RAP ship
crashing before?

15:37.806 --> 15:39.416
- You mean
other than the one

15:39.460 --> 15:42.724
your son detonated
over the bloc?

15:46.554 --> 15:48.469
That's a chopper.

15:48.512 --> 15:49.992
Sounds like a Blackhawk.

15:50.036 --> 15:52.168
- Probably
the Authority's ERT--

15:52.212 --> 15:55.780
Grayhats,
trained for quick deployment.

15:55.824 --> 15:58.958
If there's a human response,
this wasn't just an accident.

15:59.001 --> 16:01.438
Something bigger is going on.

16:01.482 --> 16:04.180
- Then we need to get
to that overlook.

16:05.703 --> 16:07.009
Let's go.

16:14.060 --> 16:16.105
- Are you sure this is
the right spot?

16:16.149 --> 16:18.978
- Unless somebody moved it.

16:43.176 --> 16:46.396
- We have to get this
to the Resistance.

16:48.877 --> 16:51.053
What if they really have
a RAP?

16:51.097 --> 16:54.274
This could be the thing
that wins the war.

16:54.317 --> 16:56.406
Don't you care?
- Of course, I care.

16:56.450 --> 16:58.669
A lot of people suffered
for this thing,

16:58.713 --> 17:00.062
maybe the whole LA colony.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.629
- Which is why we have
to use the radio.

17:01.672 --> 17:03.805
- It's too dangerous.
- A ship just crashed.

17:03.848 --> 17:06.677
There are drones everywhere.
It's already dangerous.

17:06.721 --> 17:09.593
- I hear you. That's why
we have to be extra careful.

17:09.637 --> 17:12.248
- I will be careful.

17:12.292 --> 17:15.164
Maybe the Resistance
can get us out of here.

17:17.949 --> 17:20.561
Who's in charge?

17:20.604 --> 17:22.780
You or Dad?

17:25.261 --> 17:27.437
We're all in charge.
We make decisions together.

17:27.481 --> 17:28.960
- That's not true.

17:29.004 --> 17:30.223
I know that you agree with me
about the radio.

17:30.266 --> 17:31.876
That means it's two to one.

17:31.920 --> 17:34.227
- We'll talk about it later.
- You know I'm right, Mom.

17:34.270 --> 17:37.230
If we stay here,
the RAPs are gonna find us,

17:37.273 --> 17:40.450
and everything that you did
will be for nothing.

17:40.494 --> 17:47.240
♪

17:53.246 --> 17:56.118
We can't go out there.
They'll spot us.

17:56.162 --> 17:58.120
- Right now
they got bigger fish to fry.

17:58.164 --> 18:00.079
- You want to bet
your life on that?

18:00.122 --> 18:01.689
- What do you think's
gonna happen

18:01.732 --> 18:03.343
if they cordon up this area
and end up catching us?

18:03.386 --> 18:05.171
You're a former proxy
who went rogue

18:05.214 --> 18:07.477
with the most wanted resistance
group in Los Angeles.

18:07.521 --> 18:09.566
- I'll just tell them
that you kidnapped me.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.351
I can be very convincing.

18:11.394 --> 18:13.483
- We're going
to that observation deck,

18:13.527 --> 18:16.225
and you're gonna tell me
exactly what you see.

18:16.269 --> 18:17.922
Come on.

18:17.966 --> 18:19.402
- Okay.

18:19.446 --> 18:20.925
Ah!

18:20.969 --> 18:28.194
♪

18:58.354 --> 18:58.528
.

18:58.572 --> 19:00.530
- Why are the drones
attacking that thing?

19:00.574 --> 19:03.185
Isn't it one of the RAP's
own ships?

19:03.229 --> 19:05.970
- Your guess is
as good as mine.

19:08.277 --> 19:11.498
[gunfire, explosions
in the distance]

19:16.807 --> 19:19.419
- It doesn't look like
one of the Hosts' ships.

19:19.462 --> 19:21.203
They're usually
less streamlined.

19:27.862 --> 19:31.822
- There was a rumor at the IGA
about the Factory.

19:32.693 --> 19:34.347
Some people thought
it was designed

19:34.390 --> 19:36.958
to build
space-based weapons.

19:43.443 --> 19:45.749
The RAPs have enemies?

19:47.403 --> 19:49.144
We were in a cabin
for six goddamn months

19:49.188 --> 19:50.711
and you never
thought to mention that?

19:50.754 --> 19:53.192
- There were a million stories
flying around the IGA.

19:53.235 --> 19:56.195
Did you expect me to repeat
every rumor that I heard?

19:56.238 --> 19:59.328
- I'm looking at
a lot more than a rumor.

19:59.372 --> 20:01.678
Maybe the RAPs are at war.

20:01.722 --> 20:03.898
Maybe that ship
came here to attack them.

20:03.941 --> 20:05.943
- Or maybe a group of humans
stole a RAP ship

20:05.987 --> 20:08.337
that I haven't seen before,
and it just got shot down.

20:08.381 --> 20:10.121
There's no way to know.

20:10.165 --> 20:11.732
- This is huge.

20:11.775 --> 20:13.473
Suppose you're right,
and there is a war.

20:13.516 --> 20:15.257
We'd just be
a bunch of cavemen

20:15.301 --> 20:16.911
stuck in the middle
throwing rocks.

20:16.954 --> 20:19.130
- Or maybe we find an ally.

20:19.174 --> 20:21.611
The enemy of my enemy
is my friend.

20:21.655 --> 20:23.526
- That's the same logic
the Japanese used

20:23.570 --> 20:25.528
when they sided
with the Nazis.

20:25.572 --> 20:29.010
As I remember, it didn't
exactly work out well for them.

20:35.190 --> 20:37.714
We got to get out of here.

20:40.761 --> 20:47.507
♪

20:50.292 --> 20:51.859
- Oh, we might not
be going anywhere.

20:51.902 --> 20:53.556
We'll decide when
your father gets back.

20:53.600 --> 20:55.776
- I don't want to go back
to Los Angeles.

20:55.819 --> 20:56.951
- Neither do I.

20:56.994 --> 20:59.388
We'll find another place,
a safe place.

21:00.650 --> 21:02.826
- Let's take it
one step at a time.

21:02.870 --> 21:04.437
If we have to leave,

21:04.480 --> 21:07.701
we'll start by going
to the house down the hill.

21:11.400 --> 21:13.837
- Why can't we just
get rid of that thing?

21:15.361 --> 21:17.754
- Because it's important.

21:17.798 --> 21:19.582
- But they'll stop
following us.

21:19.626 --> 21:21.671
That's important, too.

21:26.110 --> 21:28.417
- We've kept that thing
because we don't want

21:28.461 --> 21:30.593
you and your brothers
to have to live like this

21:30.637 --> 21:32.291
for the rest of your lives.

21:32.334 --> 21:34.858
♪

21:34.902 --> 21:36.991
Maybe...

21:37.644 --> 21:40.342
Maybe it can help us get back
to the way we used to live--

21:40.386 --> 21:41.343
to the old world.

21:41.387 --> 21:43.345
- That world's gone.

21:43.389 --> 21:49.656
♪

22:00.580 --> 22:02.712
- Lead team approaching
position one.

22:02.756 --> 22:05.062
Do we have eyes in the sky?

22:06.455 --> 22:07.456
- That's a negative.

22:07.500 --> 22:08.979
Air support is circling,

22:09.023 --> 22:12.156
but we don't want to alert
the target.

22:12.200 --> 22:13.549
- Copy that.

22:29.609 --> 22:36.572
♪

22:39.706 --> 22:41.490
- What do you think
those RAPs are gonna do

22:41.534 --> 22:42.926
when they're done
destroying that ship?

22:42.970 --> 22:46.190
- Not exactly talking
about my area of expertise.

22:46.234 --> 22:48.845
- If anything escaped,
they're gonna want to find it.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.673
Back in the Rangers, we
would've secured the perimeter

22:50.717 --> 22:52.632
and then covered every square
inch of that landing zone.

22:52.675 --> 22:54.198
- I still think
it's better to hide.

22:54.242 --> 22:56.418
Those drones are gonna be
in search-and-destroy.

22:56.462 --> 22:57.724
They'll shoot anything
that moves.

22:57.767 --> 22:59.508
You know, maybe--
maybe we should--

22:59.552 --> 23:02.511
indistinct chatter]

23:02.555 --> 23:09.779
♪

23:10.650 --> 23:12.608
- We want them alive
if possible.

23:12.652 --> 23:14.001
Everyone understand that?

23:14.044 --> 23:16.525
- Yeah.

23:16.569 --> 23:19.702
They're preparing
to hit the cabin.

23:19.746 --> 23:22.444
Run ahead and tell Katie
to meet at the rally point.

23:22.488 --> 23:24.664
I'll draw their fire.

23:25.926 --> 23:27.406
Move!

23:27.449 --> 23:31.627
♪

23:31.671 --> 23:34.195
- Shit! Take cover!
Take cover!

23:34.238 --> 23:36.066
- He's over there!

23:39.113 --> 23:44.901
♪

23:48.514 --> 23:48.905
.

23:51.604 --> 23:56.826
♪

23:56.870 --> 23:58.306
Jesus.

23:58.349 --> 24:00.177
- Grayhats.

24:00.221 --> 24:02.179
- I don't know. Too many.

24:02.223 --> 24:04.007
- I got the kids.

24:04.051 --> 24:05.792
Do what you need to do.

24:05.835 --> 24:09.099
♪

24:09.143 --> 24:11.362
Hi, guys.

24:11.406 --> 24:14.104
I need you to follow me, okay?

24:14.148 --> 24:15.802
- Uh, you know the game
hide

24:15.845 --> 24:17.194
- I don't want
to play that game.

24:17.238 --> 24:18.369
They're shooting guns.

24:18.413 --> 24:20.197
- Yes, which is why
we have to go.

24:20.241 --> 24:22.504
- Emergency plan.

24:22.548 --> 24:24.027
♪

24:24.071 --> 24:27.988
- Ten bogies outside, at least.

24:28.031 --> 24:30.512
God damn it!

24:30.556 --> 24:32.601
We got to clear out.

24:32.645 --> 24:39.913
♪

24:45.440 --> 24:47.486
Kids?

24:54.754 --> 25:02.022
♪

25:07.462 --> 25:09.682
- Two minutes.

25:11.118 --> 25:14.469
[gunfire playing
over speakers]

25:15.818 --> 25:17.733
- Wait.

25:17.777 --> 25:20.301
Okay, go.
Go, go.

25:23.130 --> 25:30.354
♪

25:45.021 --> 25:52.289
♪

26:02.996 --> 26:04.563
Gracie.

26:04.606 --> 26:05.607
Get 'em moving.

26:05.651 --> 26:08.088
- Honey, come with me.
Come on.

26:08.131 --> 26:15.356
♪

26:36.856 --> 26:38.901
- Katie!

26:38.945 --> 26:40.337
Katie.

26:40.381 --> 26:43.776
- I'm okay.
I think it hit my backpack.

26:43.819 --> 26:47.693
Oh.

26:47.736 --> 26:49.695
- We're clear.

26:53.002 --> 26:55.526
[gunfire playing
over speakers]

26:57.311 --> 27:00.270
[Handel's "The Arrival
of the Queen of Sheba" plays]

27:00.314 --> 27:06.233
♪

27:06.276 --> 27:08.409
- We need to buy more time
for Snyder and the kids.

27:08.452 --> 27:10.759
- We're just about
out of tricks.

27:10.803 --> 27:12.021
Bram, go and help them.

27:12.065 --> 27:13.544
We'll try and slow down
the Grayhats.

27:13.588 --> 27:14.415
Give us ten minutes.

27:14.458 --> 27:15.634
If we aren't there by then,

27:15.677 --> 27:17.374
get to the backup cabin
and hole up.

27:17.418 --> 27:19.115
We'll meet you there.

27:19.159 --> 27:20.639
You good?
- Yeah.

27:20.682 --> 27:22.249
- Let's go.

27:22.292 --> 27:29.560
♪

27:46.926 --> 27:54.194
♪

27:55.630 --> 27:57.153
Come on.

28:02.768 --> 28:05.379
- Yeah. I'm glad you're here.

28:05.422 --> 28:07.424
Get them in the truck.

28:07.468 --> 28:09.688
- To help your parents.

28:09.731 --> 28:13.126
- I don't know, but I owe them.

28:17.957 --> 28:25.225
♪

28:40.283 --> 28:42.285
♪

28:42.329 --> 28:44.113
- Shots fired!

28:44.157 --> 28:46.463
♪

28:48.335 --> 28:49.945
- Keep low.

28:49.989 --> 28:51.773
- Got movement. Down there.

28:51.817 --> 28:53.775
- Copy that.

28:53.819 --> 28:55.559
- Will, that's a kill zone.

28:55.603 --> 28:57.779
- I know.
Stay with me.

28:59.346 --> 29:00.913
- Yeah.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.527
♪

29:08.181 --> 29:09.835
- Hold your fire!

29:09.878 --> 29:16.929
♪

29:52.834 --> 29:55.750
- What--

29:58.579 --> 30:00.102
- Not the first time.

30:01.974 --> 30:04.063
- Come on, let's go.

30:04.106 --> 30:07.414
♪

30:12.027 --> 30:12.462
.

30:17.946 --> 30:21.254
- They're in the back.
- Good, we got to get moving.

30:22.342 --> 30:24.126
- He went back for you.

30:26.476 --> 30:29.392
We wait for him?

30:29.436 --> 30:31.264
- We can't.

30:31.307 --> 30:34.093
He knows where to meet us.

30:40.099 --> 30:41.927
You guys all right?

30:41.970 --> 30:43.145
Hold on.

30:43.189 --> 30:50.413
♪

31:11.086 --> 31:13.915
- Hold it right there. Hold it!

31:13.959 --> 31:15.438
- Give it a rest, buddy.

31:15.482 --> 31:16.918
- He's fine.

31:16.962 --> 31:19.007
- Mr. Snyder.

31:19.051 --> 31:20.879
- I called
for a rescue operation,

31:20.922 --> 31:22.924
not to be part
of a Civil War reenactment.

31:22.968 --> 31:25.187
- This doesn't look like
a secret Resistance base.

31:25.231 --> 31:26.406
- You don't say.

31:26.449 --> 31:27.929
- Then why'd you
activate the locator?

31:27.973 --> 31:31.063
- I don't know. Maybe because
a giant alien ship

31:31.106 --> 31:33.195
just got shot down
over our heads?

31:33.239 --> 31:35.284
- Strange days.

31:35.328 --> 31:38.853
None of that changes the job
that you volunteered for.

31:38.897 --> 31:41.203
- Well, I can't live
like this anymore.

31:41.247 --> 31:42.857
I'm done.

31:42.901 --> 31:45.947
- You're done
when the job is done.

31:49.429 --> 31:51.170
Well, you can have it.
It's right here.

31:51.213 --> 31:53.389
- We could've had it
before you left the Colony,

31:53.433 --> 31:55.043
and believe me, we'll get it.

31:55.087 --> 31:58.699
In the meantime, you're gonna
lead us to the missing Host.

31:58.742 --> 32:00.309
- I've been with them
for six months.

32:00.353 --> 32:03.399
They have no idea where
the Resistance base is.

32:03.443 --> 32:05.053
- Well...

32:05.097 --> 32:09.057
looks to me like we just
motivated them to go find it.

32:09.101 --> 32:10.537
Now...

32:10.580 --> 32:13.235
The locator.

32:13.279 --> 32:19.067
♪

32:19.111 --> 32:20.982
Do not turn this on again

32:21.026 --> 32:23.854
until you have eyes
on the missing Host.

32:25.987 --> 32:27.597
We're not done.

32:29.469 --> 32:33.125
Will Bowman has an excellent
reputation as an investigator.

32:34.474 --> 32:36.432
You're gonna need
a convincing cover story

32:36.476 --> 32:38.695
when you
see him again.

32:38.739 --> 32:42.221
- Ah!

33:06.680 --> 33:08.551
- Sorry, Will.

33:10.162 --> 33:12.903
We knew it wasn't
gonna last forever.

33:17.647 --> 33:20.694
We have to find Noa's camp.

33:21.695 --> 33:23.740
We owe it to Broussard.

33:23.784 --> 33:26.004
We made a promise.

33:27.396 --> 33:30.138
- Yeah, I know.

33:30.182 --> 33:31.705
I know.

33:33.402 --> 33:35.013
- Hey, Dad.

33:37.885 --> 33:39.452
- Jesus,
what happened to you?

33:39.495 --> 33:42.498
I ran into a couple Grayhats.

33:42.542 --> 33:45.284
One of them hit me
with his rifle.

33:45.327 --> 33:48.026
They probably have orders
to bring me in alive.

33:48.069 --> 33:50.071
I am a high-value target,
after all.

33:51.203 --> 33:53.031
- They walked into
a booby trap.

33:53.074 --> 33:55.555
I-I ran away,
and I didn't look back.

33:55.598 --> 33:57.513
- Sounds like you got lucky.

33:57.557 --> 33:59.167
- I don't feel lucky.

33:59.211 --> 34:02.910
♪

34:02.953 --> 34:04.564
I'm fine.
Thank you.

34:04.607 --> 34:06.044
- I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

34:06.087 --> 34:09.264
- The important thing is
no one followed me.

34:11.092 --> 34:12.876
♪

34:12.920 --> 34:16.271
- I guess I don't,
which is why we should move.

34:16.315 --> 34:19.666
- Not until you answer
some questions first.

34:19.709 --> 34:22.016
What kind of questions?

34:27.587 --> 34:29.371
I don't know.
They--

34:29.415 --> 34:30.807
they probably spotted us

34:30.851 --> 34:32.940
during the aerial survey
after the crash.

34:32.983 --> 34:34.159
- Those guys
didn't stumble on us.

34:34.202 --> 34:35.595
That was a strike team.

34:35.638 --> 34:39.207
They came here
organized and ready.

34:41.949 --> 34:44.908
We're here.
We're alive.

34:44.952 --> 34:48.216
We should just count
our blessings and move on.

34:48.260 --> 34:49.783
- After the Arrival,

34:49.826 --> 34:51.785
a lot of guys in my line
of work died counting blessings

34:51.828 --> 34:54.092
when they should've been
asking questions.

34:54.135 --> 34:56.137
♪

34:56.181 --> 34:57.834
- He helped us, Dad.

34:57.878 --> 34:59.706
He got Gracie and Charlie
in the truck,

34:59.749 --> 35:03.101
and then he went back
looking for you.

35:09.150 --> 35:12.545
- I'm just trying to do my part
and help the family.

35:12.588 --> 35:15.591
♪

35:15.635 --> 35:18.551
- We should move.

35:18.594 --> 35:20.118
- So...

35:20.161 --> 35:23.164
does that mean
that I can climb aboard?

35:26.385 --> 35:28.256
- Yeah, hop in.

35:28.300 --> 35:35.307
♪

35:45.795 --> 35:46.013
.

35:48.842 --> 35:50.409
- Hello.

35:50.452 --> 35:53.673
Whoever is listening, this is
the Los Angeles Resistance.

35:53.716 --> 35:56.545
We have the package, and we're
ready to bring it to you.

35:58.068 --> 35:59.635
- Over.

36:01.071 --> 36:05.206
- Dad said you have to say
"over" when you're done.

36:08.470 --> 36:12.039
- I repeat, this is
the Los Angeles Resistance.

36:12.082 --> 36:13.214
We're friends of the pilot.

36:13.258 --> 36:14.998
We're in danger and on the run.

36:15.042 --> 36:18.785
If you want the package, this
is your last chance to get it.

36:18.828 --> 36:20.526
Over.

36:54.951 --> 36:56.823
- I don't know.

37:05.135 --> 37:08.008
Up there, the trees.

37:08.051 --> 37:14.841
♪

37:14.884 --> 37:17.409
- What would
chop them off like that?

37:17.452 --> 37:20.847
- Whatever hit 'em.

37:20.890 --> 37:23.763
Smart thing to do would be
to get back in that truck

37:23.806 --> 37:26.156
and get the hell out of here.

37:26.200 --> 37:32.902
♪

37:41.346 --> 37:48.614
♪

38:09.374 --> 38:16.642
♪

38:28.393 --> 38:31.352
- Are you the one who was
breaking protocol?

38:33.572 --> 38:35.835
- I'll ask the questions.

38:35.878 --> 38:39.621
What are your names?
Your real names.

38:42.189 --> 38:45.497
- It's been a long time
since your secret identities

38:45.540 --> 38:47.673
were secret.

38:47.716 --> 38:50.284
What do you have to lose
at this point?

38:50.328 --> 38:54.070
♪

38:54.114 --> 38:55.594
- Bowman.

38:55.637 --> 38:59.032
My name is Bram, and my parents
are Katie and Will.

39:00.250 --> 39:02.122
- Noa mentioned your name.

39:02.165 --> 39:05.995
We've been waiting a long time
for you to make contact.

39:06.039 --> 39:08.215
There's a little bridge called
the "Middle Fork"

39:08.258 --> 39:09.695
in Smith River.

39:09.738 --> 39:11.784
Meet me there in 48 hours.

39:11.827 --> 39:13.873
And bring the package.

39:13.916 --> 39:20.967
♪

39:45.295 --> 39:48.734
♪

39:48.777 --> 39:51.650
- There's something inside.

40:06.012 --> 40:09.624
- Is that what they
look like inside the suit?

40:10.625 --> 40:12.192
- I don't know.

40:15.108 --> 40:17.284
Someone's gonna be looking
for this thing.

40:17.327 --> 40:19.460
We got to get out of here.

40:19.504 --> 40:21.201
Come on.

40:31.646 --> 40:38.914
♪
